” she said “because that diversity of thought brings a better balance to the company” zlatkus who grew up in a pittsburgh family of five girls never considered her gender an obstacle “i think i’m very driven and have a lot of passion to do well and make a difference that was my upbringing” she said “i never really thought of what i couldn’t do i always thought of the next thing i could do i am blessed with a wonderful family” related articlesunion steps up opposition to state budget cuts with new adthe hartford chief risk officer to retiremargaret y livingstoncarolyn o’connellsuper women the  women of firekathleen murphy women of fire archive select year       special sections top most popular most recenthartford attorney charged with larceny former bankruptcy attorney admits to stealing millions from clients glastonbury construction employee pleads guilty to kickback scheme ridgefield realtor arrested charged with larceny woman sentenced for stealing m from employer commercial loan growth boosts earnings at simsbury bank industrial auction announced in east hartford elevenbuilding industry park sold in north haven wells fargo to refund m to customers hit by car loan insurance doctors indicted for medicaid fraud special sections bottom executive briefing lizabeth h zlatkus by the commercial record time to read  min executive briefing use of bridgeport stamford parking fee surpluses … executive briefing conn median income down  percent in       × login this page requires a paid subscription username password forgot password   new subscriber submit